div.p:
As elaborated in Halter et al. (2019: 126), the team defined a set of requirements for the visualizations. They should
Represent visual impressions true to human perception;
Represent subtle aesthetic nuances in figure and ground separately;
Visualize the films at the micro (screenshot, temporal segment), meso (individual film) and macro (corpus) levels. And in addition they should be interactive and flexible for adjustment to an individual researcher’s interest.

